    • Enum Constant Detail

      • Create

        public static final UpdateType Create
        This operation creates a graph in the Graph Store (this operation is a NOP for bigdata). 
         CREATE ( SILENT )? GRAPH IRIref
        See Also:
        http://www.w3.org/TR/sparql11-update/#create, CreateGraph

      • Drop

        public static final UpdateType Drop
        The DROP operation removes the specified graph(s) from the Graph Store. 
         DROP  ( SILENT )? (GRAPH IRIref | DEFAULT | NAMED | ALL )
        Note: Bigdata does not support empty graphs, so Clear and Drop have the same semantics.
        See Also:
        http://www.w3.org/TR/sparql11-update/#drop, DropGraph

      • Copy

        public static final UpdateType Copy
        The COPY operation is a shortcut for inserting all data from an input graph into a destination graph. Data from the input graph is not affected, but data from the destination graph, if any, is removed before insertion. 
         COPY ( SILENT )? ( ( GRAPH )? IRIref_from | DEFAULT) TO ( ( GRAPH )? IRIref_to | DEFAULT )
        See Also:
        http://www.w3.org/TR/sparql11-update/#copy, CopyGraph

      • Move

        public static final UpdateType Move
        The MOVE operation is a shortcut for moving all data from an input graph into a destination graph. The input graph is removed after insertion and data from the destination graph, if any, is removed before insertion. 
         MOVE (SILENT)? ( ( GRAPH )? IRIref_from | DEFAULT) TO ( ( GRAPH )? IRIref_to | DEFAULT)
        See Also:
        http://www.w3.org/TR/sparql11-update/#move, MoveGraph

      • Add

        public static final UpdateType Add
        Graph management operation inserts all data from one graph into another. Data from the source graph is not effected. Data already present in the target graph is not effected. 
         ADD ( SILENT )? ( ( GRAPH )? IRIref_from | DEFAULT) TO ( ( GRAPH )? IRIref_to | DEFAULT)
        See Also:
        http://www.w3.org/TR/sparql11-update/#add, AddGraph

      • InsertData

        public static final UpdateType InsertData
        The INSERT DATA operation adds some triples, given inline in the request, into the Graph Store: 
         INSERT DATA  QuadData
        See Also:
        http://www.w3.org/TR/sparql11-update/#insertData, InsertData

      • DeleteData

        public static final UpdateType DeleteData
        The DELETE DATA operation removes some triples, given inline in the request, if the respective graphs in the Graph Store contain those: 
         DELETE DATA  QuadData
        See Also:
        http://www.w3.org/TR/sparql11-update/#deleteData, DeleteData

      • DeleteInsert

        public static final UpdateType DeleteInsert
        The DELETE/INSERT operation can be used to remove or add triples from/to the Graph Store based on bindings for a query pattern specified in a WHERE clause: 
         ( WITH IRIref )?
 ( ( DeleteClause InsertClause? ) | InsertClause )
 ( USING ( NAMED )? IRIref )*
 WHERE GroupGraphPattern
        The DeleteClause and InsertClause forms can be broken down as follows: 
         DeleteClause ::= DELETE  QuadPattern 
 InsertClause ::= INSERT  QuadPattern
        See Also:
        http://www.w3.org/TR/sparql11-update/#deleteInsert, DeleteInsertGraph

      • Load

        public static final UpdateType Load
        The LOAD operation reads an RDF document from a IRI and inserts its triples into the specified graph in the Graph Store. 
         LOAD ( SILENT )? IRIref_from ( INTO GRAPH IRIref_to )?
        See Also:
        http://www.w3.org/TR/sparql11-update/#load, LoadGraph

      • Clear

        public static final UpdateType Clear
        The CLEAR operation removes all the triples in the specified graph(s) in the Graph Store. 
         CLEAR  ( SILENT )? (GRAPH IRIref | DEFAULT | NAMED | ALL )
        Note: Bigdata does not support empty graphs, so Clear and Drop have the same semantics.
        See Also:
        http://www.w3.org/TR/sparql11-update/#clear, ClearGraph

      • DropEntailments

        public static final UpdateType DropEntailments
        The DROP ENTAILMENTS operation drop the entailments. This is only required if you have removed some statements from the database.

      • CreateEntailments

        public static final UpdateType CreateEntailments
        The CREATE ENTAILMENTS operation compute the entailments using an efficient "database-at-once" closure operation.

      • DisableEntailments

        public static final UpdateType DisableEntailments
        The DISABLE ENTAILMENTS operation can be used to disable incremental truth maintenance.

      • EnableEntailments

        public static final UpdateType EnableEntailments
        The ENABLE ENTAILMENTS operation can be used to enable incremental truth maintenance.
